///
/// Introduction
@node INTRO "OpusNIbar   ·   Introduction"


  ···········································
@{fg shine}  WHAT IS OPUSNIBAR?@{fg text}
  ···········································

  OpusNIbar is a set of NewIcons for use with
  the toolbar in Directory Opus 5.5 or higher.


@{b}  Why another pack of Toolbar icons?@{ub}

  I was looking for toolbar icons on Aminet,
  but I didn't like the look of any of them.

  So I felt like doing something about this,
  and this is the result - 146 fresh, clean
  and colorful icons, all for free.

  @{i}Enjoy!@{ui}


@endnode
///
/// Requirements
@node NEEDS "OpusNIbar   ·   Requirements"

  ···········································
@{fg shine}  REQUIREMENTS FOR OPUSNIBAR.@{fg text}
  ···········································

@{b}  Required:@{ub}

   · An Amiga with AmigaOS 2.04+
   · Directory Opus 5.5 or higher.
   · NewIcons installed.


@{b}  Recommended@{ub} (but not required):

   · AmigaOS 3.0+
   · 32 Colors or more on screen (GFX Card).
   · A display mode with square (1:1) pixels.
   · The faster Amiga the better.

@endnode
///
/// Installation
@node INSTALL "OpusNIbar   ·   Installation"

  ·······················································
@{fg shine}  THE INSTALLATION OF OPUSNIBAR.@{fg text}
  ·······················································

  This is quite easy, just copy the 'images' drawer to
  anywhere you like, you'll probably like it to be inside
  the Dopus5: drawer.


  @{b}NOTE!@{ub}
  The 'ToolBarArrow.image' needs to be in Dopus5:Images/.
  Opus doesn't support it in Icon-format, so it has to
  be an AnimBrush.


@endnode
